		<hr size="1">i know bards are good at PvP, and i can think of a few good ways of winning in PvP situation, but id love some advice for my 30s bard to PvP.  mainly vs SKs, Nec, Chanter, Wiz, Mage classes.  shammy and BL too for that matter.</P><P>we have great resist buff songs when played with a drum that are awsome.</P><P>selo's duh...</P><P>chants duh...</P><P>mez...</P><P>few other questions.</P><P>do macros still work when you have been blinded, or do you have to double tap with alt+gem?</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
