		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 9/23/2003 2:49:05 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=62449">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Tolain Durant" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="mailto:danjnwo5@yahoo.com" target="_new">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/email.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Email Tolain Durant" width="24" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Tolain+Durant">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Tolain Durant" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2034112&TN=bards+in+PvP&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2034331&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Bards are simply godlike in PvP, but heres the problem.</P><P>Until 50ish, you dont have the chants to do decent damage. Before that point you are just hard to kill, not overly offensive.</P><P>Macros should work, the trick is to never let blind land. Blind stops landing around 50 MR if I remember from my SZ days.</P><P>Its hard at low levels, but once you get psalm of veeshan, and all resists are like 400ish, nothing ever stops you. 2.5 minute selos, and dispel song, as well as your Mana drain song (800 mana drained a cast with puretone, almost unresistable!)</P><P>I'll keep in mind the level, but it'll be hard. BBB will interupt casting ALOT if it works, so will mez. so try to interupt them with those.</P><P><BR>SKs- keep MR up, stay out of range and try to land fufills and chant of fire. Charm mobs on him, use MMM to keep out of melee range should you get snared. keep HP above 75%</P><P>Nec- I think charming pets disabled now..A good necro will be shadowstepping while he baits you with the pet and dots you, and lifetaps. the taps are very hard to resist. Pumice pumice pumice! Knock his dots off with pumice/dispels, and kill the pet if its annoying. He wont have the time or mana to make a new one. then melee, throw pets at him, and keep pumicing</P><P>Necros generally arent a threat once you have the tools to render their dots useless. If mez lands, sap him dry with denons mana drain. If snare lands and you dont want to fight the pet, mez him and MMM while healing. If the necro decides to lifetap/nuke you down, he'll usually burn himself out of mana fast.</P><P>PVP necros are one scale or another. they'll either have great resists and nonexistant HP amounts, or decent HP/mana, and no resists. Know which type your up against, and plan accordingly.</P><P>Chanter- I hate these guys... they'll debuff your MR a bit. Buy a dot potion and quaff it before the fight so you wont get mezzed. Keep MR up to avoid nukes, dispel their debuffs/buffs, and snare and melee them. try interuptions with BBB</P><P>Wiz- A battle of endurance. You regen faster than he meds. dance in and out of spell range while hitting him with dots. if you fall to 50%, run and heal, come back and continue the fight. continue until he drops.</P><P>Mage- Keep FR/MR song up, if he cant land any spells, there is no risk. Dont get hit by the earth pet, a root is bad. Just kill their pet at your own leisure, then melee/chant the mage down</P><P>shammy- A battle that takes forever. Only battles I've had that lasted longer are against paladins. They'll either go all out on dots- see necro. or heal themselves alot.</P><P>BL-Their spells arent enough to phase you, so just stay away from the pet and dot/dd them down. avoid melee except for quick bursts<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
