		<hr size="1">Hmm, thats true, but I mean in the +150 range. Thats when dots are hard to land. most players in pvp have fire, ice, and magic resist as their prime 3..usually over 200 too. but disease and poison almost always drop under 100 if they do that. If for some reason their poison and disease resists are high, it usually means they dropped fr/cr/mr, and you can selo away and switch chants.</P><P>Isnt paladin innate disease resist only ~5 or so? My last main character was a paladin, I never remembered it being too significant. Of course, this is a blue server too.</P><P>I hate to take the "bluebies don't know how to fight" stance that all the jerks use, but it tends to be very very true. They most likely wont be prepared for combat, wont have a full resist suit, pumices, and the like, so worry about your resists compared to the enemies class, thats basically 90% of the fight, imo.</P><P>Message edited by: Tolain Durant (9/27/2003 11:45:41 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
