		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2034112&TN=bards+in+PvP&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2042386&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">bellow isn't stun, its knockback in the direction YOU are facing.</P><P>Brusco`s Boastful Bellow<BR>1: Decrease Hit Points (HP) from 7 (L12) to 31 (L60)</P><P><BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Classes: Brd (L12)</P><P>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Skill: Singing<BR>Allowable Targets: All<BR>Beneficial: Detrimental</P><P>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Range to Target: 100.00 feet<BR>Pushes Target Back: 1.00 feet</P><P><BR>so if they are in a corner and you are beating on them it wont push them anywhere and will rarely interupt casting if they have decent channeling. if they back themselves into a wall get as close to on top of them as you can, face away from the corner and try turning attack on, usually(at least used to work) you could still melee them and bellow to push them away from the wall</P><P>one problem is the range on it is only 100 feet, where as most casters spells are 200</P><P>as for resistablility....at 51 i get maybe 1 resist every 4-8 fights....its just a dd for resist purposes</P><P><BR>speed is your advantage, joust them(dance around opponents)...if they call you gay or say you are fighting like a pussy you are probably doing it well and they are frustrated <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle>.....try to circle around them(mouse drive for that) and turn auto attack on to hit them with a round of of melee then turn auto attack off and get out of the way(gogo selos) before they can turn auto attack on for melees</P><P>selo's/snare(if its landing), bellow, bellow</P><P>our dots are actually relatively effective, i was able to kill a war 1 lvl lower than me with them using a drum and still dancing around meleeing(gogo 8pt punch kill shot woowoo)</P><P>as for blind not landing on 50+ mr....maybe i just get super unlucky but it lands on me about 1 in 4 with 120 mr from anyone within a few lvls of me.  it may only stick for a couple seconds but it kills werewolf illusion which blows</P><P><BR>sks....try to entice them into using HT early in the fight, then let just treat them like a war with a little better regen(from those pesky taps) and use track incase they shadowstep and you cant find them(beware sometimes track gets bugged, seems to happen most in hilly areas to me)</P><P>nec....dot kite pet(pets are dumb npcs always kite them they dont know better than to chase you), bellow,bellow,bellow,bellow(oh yeah and melee and bellow), heal as needed(if you get darked/rooted dispell immediately, use track incase they shadow step and you cant find them)<BR>spells to keep up</P><P>wiz....if you can keep healing up try to keep yourself as high on hp as possible for those pesky crits and bellow, track incase of shadowstep.  try to stay next to them so if they rain or snare it will hit them too(they may resist but they may not)</P><P>mage...they are a wizard with gimp nukes, no root, no snare, and no shadowstep and a easily kiteable pet to make up for it.  kite the pet with chants, stay next to them to avoid them using rains, bellow, heal as needed, laugh at them, the usual</P><P>shammy..chant kite the pet keep pr/dr/mr song up to counter dots/slow and just eat the cold nukes.  once you get them low it'll take forever b/c they'll chain heal but in the end you should win</P><P>bl.....well i havent actually fought too many BLs, kite the pet, blind sucks but what can you do....you can try mr but it just doesnt do much.  their dots and nukes are relatively weak i believe, as are their player heals, they do however have good pet heals so if you can, get their pet away from them to kill it</P><P>its hard to really choose 8 slots to use for any class in pvp, but these can be useful<BR>selos<BR>snare(eventually it lands and makes jousting soooo much easier)<BR>bellow<BR>possible mez, but it can be unreliable, or possibly heal<BR>haste if you're fighting a caster<BR>chant of flame<BR>mmm/possibly resist/ds song/haste<BR>mmm/possibly resist/ds song/haste</P><P>at 51 what i use is<BR>dispell<BR>bellow<BR>snare<BR>selo<BR>fire dot<BR>ice dot<BR>disease dot<BR>poison dot</P><P>occasionally i switch out one dot(fire/ice) for another spell, but thats my general line-up while im just out hunting</P><P>if you use mmm be sure not to be somewhere you are going to aggro mobs on yourself</P><P>as for charming, personally i dont do it because if they get low and your charm breaks they are likely to get aggro and die an xp death, or if your charm breaks right as you get snared and you are low you culd die and lose xp</P><P><BR>keep in mind bards dont have to stop running/meleeing to cast spells, so a few useful items</P><P>crystallized pumice, 5 charges of nullify magic</P><P>little utalized item, holgresh mojo sticks.  they drop off mid 30s flying monkeys in wakening lands.  while your bard may not be able to kill them(they are casters fyi) if you have a higher lvl char you could farm them.  the sticks themselves have 5 charges of a mage/wizzy spell that can do up to 270 dmg with like 4-5 sec cast(depends on their resists and which mojo stick you get, beware some are pb ae spells)  i used to have about 3 backpacks full of those, nothing like getting tells from people i was pking "you're so lucky that wizzy showed up to save you" back when in was 20s-low 30s</P><P>dot potions are a good idea as was mentioned</P><P>if you happen to have one i'd imagine bio orb would be good if they have low mr, but i would imagine those are still semi-expensive</P><P>assuming not too much has changed in the game in the past 6 months or so this should help</P><P>p.s. if you wanna lvl to 45 get a singing steel bp, right click 100 hp 6 sec cast....eliminates needing to have heal song memmed or lvl to 40 for dispell song and lute of the howler(40% haste, 40ish atk, 30str)</P><P>best of luck to ya</P><P>macros still work, however i rarely use them, alt+# works just fine for me /shrug</P><P><BR>edits: im really tired and screwing things up, if i missed something maybe i'll correct it tomorrow ^_^</P><P><BR>"Eagles may soar, but weasels don't get sucked into jet engines."<BR>"If you want a bug fixed, find a way to exploit it."</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=58519">Tarzom Ubarelf</a> &lt;<a href="http://www.darkdefiantwarriors.com/">Dark Defiant Warriors</a>><BR>Minstrel of the 51st song<BR>Vallon Zek<BR>Semi-retired</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49349">Relyna</a><BR>Preserver of the 57th season<BR>Vallon Zek<BR>Retired</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49262">Sage Raabe Soulshifter</a> &lt;<a href="http://www.aduentus.net/">Aduentus</a>><BR>Human Warlock of the 62nd moon<BR>Vallon Zek<BR>Retired</P><P>Message edited by: Raabe Soulshifter (10/7/2003 12:44:29 AM)</P><P>Message edited by: Raabe Soulshifter (10/7/2003 12:46:06 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
