		<hr size="1">I had forgotten about bellow being a push componnet rather than a stun (Since the other bellow I use IS a stun)</P><P>But I still find Dots far more effective than jousting. Once you get to the high 50s or so, jousting becomes a total waste of time unless its against casters (and why joust casters? just straight melee)</P><P>Because alot of the time the opposition is packing windblades and the like, and bards are simply not cut out to trade hits against two handers.</P><P>FoL has no resist adjustment on it, so against decent resists, it simply never lands.</P><P>I dont bother with snare anymore, I'm too bloody fast for them to catch anyway :p</P><P>Put elemental and gaurdian rythems up as an idea. those two with a drum will add 100 to fire and ice, and close to 200 to MR, plus your base resists. Honestly at this point, nothing but lures and negative adjust spells land.</P><P>The SKs that screw up track is a method called "Hill bugging". We can do it as well. Good for fighting rangers <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>resists have gotten the works over the last 6 months. at one point snares cutoff was 120 MR, then it was 180, then 200 for awhile. They never changed it back for the pvp servers, so its currently based on your resists - resist modifier<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
