		<hr size="1">I just found it alot more efficient to work in 4 chants rather than jousting. Maybe its just me, but jousting cut into my twisting ability a bit.</P><P>Bards are great in the way that we have so many possible styles. My style is keeping resists high, dancing out of spell range, and assaulting them with dots.</P><P>Your right about unskilled players though. SZ it seems everyone knows how to play really well, But VZ was like a cold war. That was the saddest pvp server I've ever seen.</P><P>Although I have to hand it to some of the evils, I ran into some great players when fighting them. the three team players all just seemed to suck.</P><P></P><P>[edit] also, if your jousting, you cant have a drum equipped... That cuts your dot damage by over half. (depending on how good your drum is)</P><P>Message edited by: Tolain Durant (10/7/2003 7:12:10 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
